# Files Claude Code copies into each new git worktree it creates
# (`claude --worktree`, subagent `isolation: worktree`, desktop parallel sessions).
# Uses .gitignore syntax. Only paths that are ALSO gitignored are copied, so
# tracked files are never duplicated. See https://code.claude.com/docs/en/worktrees
#
# Why node_modules: a fresh worktree starts with no node_modules, so the
# lefthook-installed git hooks (which resolve the binary via
# <worktree>/node_modules/lefthook-*/bin/lefthook) print "Can't find lefthook in
# PATH" at commit time. Copying node_modules makes hooks, biome, and tsc work
# immediately without a manual `bun install`. Run `bun install` in the worktree
# if package.json/bun.lock drift on the branch.
node_modules/

